definitions.definition: A conurbation in North East England encompassing the towns of Middlesbrough , Stockton-on-Tees , Redcar and surrounding settlements.
A county borough of North Riding of Yorkshire which had a brief existence between 1968 and 1974, being absorbed into the County of Cleveland .
